<br />The reason I think it deserves a five is because I got hooked several times.  There was a great book if you like fairy tales and mysterious books.  </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The Lost Years of Merlin</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
                      /
                      <span>3</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-11-03</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>     In The Lost years of Merlin, a boy suddenly washes up on the shore. He awakes, not being able, his name, his paresnts, his childhood, anything. As the years go on, the boy is raised by a woman who calls herself Branwen. She also says that she is his mother and that his name is Emrys. He is always struggling to find out his real life, and his purpose. Emrys is also frequently bullied by some children that think he and his mother are evil. eventually, They move to a distant land, and Emrys soon starts his adventure, even though his body bestows many hindering disabilities.
<br />     Emrys makes some new companions, Trouble, a hawk, Rhia, a girl of the forset Drummawood, and Shim, a giant who is actually very small. Together, the four of them strive to protect the isle of Fincayra. In the end, the party reaches a great castle in the sky. here is where Emrys learns the horrible truth about his past, the one that he had been searching for.
<br />     I really hope you read this book; it is a magnificent piece of writing that can introduce a whole new meaning of magic and fantasy to any reader. I really think that the book, The Lost Years of Merlin, is appropriate for all ages, but I would highly recomend it for adults and adolescents. People of younger ages might get bored a little to easy with the plot, while older people can truely enjoy a well written piece of literature. I really enjoyed the book; it was truely inspiring and very interesting. Although the plot is a little slow at first, towards the middle of the story, it gets very fast-paced and becomes very deep. I hope that you will enjoy this book, as well as the rest of the series as much as I do.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Certainly, Definitely, Absolutely a great book</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
